==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oroheliograph
<hw>Or`o*he"li*o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'o`ros</grk> mountain + <ets>helio-</ets> +
<ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>A camera for
obtaining a circular panoramic view of the horizon. The photographic
plate is placed horizontally with a vertical lens above. A mirror of
peculiar shape reflects light from the entire horizon to the lens, by
means of which it is focused upon the plate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orohippus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
